What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you're a chemical engineer, you have to take this class. If you have an engineering bent in your interests, this class will introduce you to a lot of what makes engineering possible, all the real-life calculations and considerations that you have to make. However, like engineering classes in general, I feel, it errs on the side of throwing a lot of tools at you instead of really teaching science.
